The woman was finally judged guilty.
那个女人最终被判有罪。

裁决；评判：
Will you judge the oratorical contest next week?
你愿意担任下周演讲比赛的评判员吗?

He's good at judging wines.
他擅长鉴别葡萄酒。
It's up to you to judge these works of art.
由你们负责对这些艺术品做出评价。
断定，判断：
Don't judge a person by appearances.
不要以貌取人。
I can't judge who is right.
我无法断定谁是对的。
认为：
It was judged better to set out at once.
大家认为立刻出发比较好。
估计，估价：
We judged the distance to be about 10miles.
我们估计有 10 英里的距离。
批评，指责：
You had little cause to judge him so harshly.
你没有什么理由这样严厉地批评他。
(犹太士师)统治，管理

You should be able to judge between right and wrong.

to judge between two combatants
在两个竞技者间裁决胜负
做出评价：
Don't judge from appearances.
不要以貌取人。

grave²
